f frugivorous and nectarivorous bats by allowing them to use ephemeral food resources over a wide span of time. By sampling across phyllostomid genera, we show that patterns of apparent ethanol tolerance in New World bats are broad, and thus may have been an important early step in the evolution of frugivory and nectarivory in these animals.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Orbach, Dara N.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Veselka, Nina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Dzal, Yvonne", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lazure, Louis", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fenton, M. Brock", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Thomas, Adrian L.R.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/089803eb0f421af2fad05bedd08d5bd6", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/64f8df306f15cbd74e842146fc5ed1de51ace920f0b7911efc1b8154f6f4d149", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/3JCQTXLU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/3JCQTXLU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/3214366acc479441e5cdc51bce323a76!/b153938-156398", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "2", "pages": "e8993", "title": "PLoS ONE", "volume": "5"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/0